## Monitoring

### View Logs
```bash
# All services
tail -f logs/*.log

# Individual services
tail -f logs/gateway.log
tail -f logs/user.log
tail -f logs/admin.log
tail -f logs/ml.log
tail -f logs/prediction.log
```

### Monitor System Resources
```bash
# Memory usage (watch for OOM)
watch -n 1 'free -h'

# CPU usage
top

# Python processes (should see 50-100 at 100 VUs)
watch -n 1 'ps aux | grep python3 | wc -l'

# Disk I/O (sync logging causes writes)
iostat -x 1
```

### Check Service Health
```bash
# Gateway health check
curl http://localhost:7764/api/health

# Individual service health
curl http://localhost:3001/health  # User
curl http://localhost:3002/health  # ML
curl http://localhost:3003/health  # Admin
curl http://localhost:3004/health  # Prediction
```

### Verify Bottlenecks Are Active
```bash
# 1. Sync logging file should be growing
ls -lh logs/gateway-requests-sync.log
tail -f logs/gateway-requests-sync.log

# 2. MongoDB pool size in logs (should show 10)
grep -i "maxPoolSize" logs/gateway.log

# 3. Request queue disabled (should show UNLIMITED)
grep -i "UNLIMITED" logs/ml.log

# 4. Rate limiting active (should see in logs)
grep -i "rate limit" logs/gateway.log
```

---

## Management

### Restart Individual Service
```bash
# Find PID
cat logs/gateway.pid

# Kill process
kill <PID>

# Restart
nohup node microservices/gateway/gateway.js > logs/gateway.log 2>&1 &
echo $! > logs/gateway.pid
```

### Clean Logs and Temp Files
```bash
# Logs
rm -f logs/*.log

# Sync logging file (bottleneck)
rm -f logs/gateway-requests-sync.log

# Temp files
rm -rf tmp/*
```

### Reset Database (Optional)
```bash
# Drop database (CAUTION: Deletes all data)
mongosh "mongodb://admin:2711297449072@172.29.156.41:27017/urine-disease-detection?authSource=admin" --eval "db.dropDatabase()"
```

